@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Frequently Asked Questions";
}
<h2>@ViewBag.Title</h2>

<h4>General</h4>

<ol>
    <li>Are the tour rates inclusive of tax and service charge?
        <ul>
            <li>
                The rate shown on the website is GST included. There are some add-on charges (if applicable) such as accommodation upgrade,
                meal, equipment or any other charges. Meal, equipment or any other add-on is not included unless stated. To check the rate
                with all the charges, please select a tour and proceed to the Booking Details page, you will see the breakdown of the rate on
                the right. Please double check your booking details and grand total before paying for your tour.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Why is there more than one rate for the same tour?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Different rates are due to the different promotions being offered by a tour operator at any given time.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Why has the tour rate changed?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Our tour operators have the ability to change rates and promotions at any time.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Do you offer special discounts for seniors, students or children?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Most of the tours have special rates for seniors, students and children.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Any discount for group booking?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Discount might be given for group booking of more than a certain amount of people set by the tour operator. However it’s only applicable to certain tours at any given time. This usually stated in the tour description.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Is meal, equipment or accommodation included in the tour?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Meal, equipment, accommodation or any other add-on is not included unless stated.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        How do I know my booking has been successful?
        <ul>
            <li>
                You will receive a confirmation email with the tour details within 30 minutes after you have made a booking. Should you not receive it after 30 minutes, please check your junk mail and/or spam filters.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Do I need to print out my booking details before attending a tour?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Yes. You should print out your booking details and show it to your tour operator on the day of your tour. Note: concession or student must bring your card with you on that day. Otherwise, you might not be allowed to join the tour.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Do I need travel insurance?
        <ul>
            <li>
                We strongly recommend all participants to have personal travel insurance. Travosaur or tour operators will not be responsible for the expenditure coverage of any accidents to any participants resulting in injuries during the trip. Please go to our Travel Insurance section for further information.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Can I make a reservation directly through the tour operator?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Yes. However the rates listed on Travosaur.com website are only available through our service. Rates offered directly from tour operators are typically higher.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Can I bring my pet?
        <ul>
            <li>
                No pets are allowed to ensure guest comfort and tour quality.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Can I write a review?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Yes. You must sign up to write a review. It’s free to sign up. By signing up, you can view current or history of the tours you have booked, and it will make your online booking much easier than ever. Click here to sign up now.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        What should I do if I lost my personal belongs during the tour
        <ul>
            <li>
                The tour operator will not be responsible for any losses of your personal belongings or luggage. Please look after your personal belongings. Any losses should be reported to the police.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>


<h4>Payment</h4>
<ol>
    <li>
        Do you accept debit card or bank transfer?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Travosaur only accepts credit card and Paypal. You are required to enter your credit card details or login to your PayPal account upon completing the booking. Currently, all other payment methods are not acceptable.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
        Is it safe to enter my credit card details?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Travosaur uses Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology to encrypt your credit card details. All the sensitive information will be encrypted before sending across to the intended recipient via a secured connection.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h4>Change my Booking</h4>
<ol>
    <li>
        Can I change my booking dates?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Please refer to the terms and conditions of the tour which can be found in the tour details, or booking confirmation email if you have completed a booking. Some tour operators require at least 7 days of notice before the day of the tour. You may be charged 75-100% of full tour fare for cancellation/amendment fee as stated in the terms and conditions.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Can I transfer my booking to another person?
        <ul>
            <li>
                You will need to contact and negotiate with the tour operator directly as soon as possible.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h4>Cancellation & Refund</h4>
<ol>
    <li>
        Can I cancel my booking?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Please refer to the terms and conditions of the tour which can be found in the tour details, or booking confirmation email if you have completed a booking. Most tour operators require at least 7 days (or more) of notice before the day of the tour. You may be charged 75-100% of full tour fare for cancellation/amendment fee as stated in the terms and conditions. Bookings under promotion usually have a very strict cancellation policy which often results in a full charge.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        How to cancel my booking?
        <ul>
            <li>
                You will need to contact and negotiate with the tour operator directly as soon as possible.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Where can I find the cancellation policy?
        <ul>
            <li>
                The cancellation policy or terms and conditions can be found right under the tour description and every page of the booking form. It will also be stated in the confirmation email sent to you. Terms and conditions in the cancellation policy will be different for each booking depending on the tour. Please read this carefully before completing a tour.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Can I cancel any add-on after my booking is confirmed?
        <ul>
            <li>
                No. Add-on cannot be cancelled once a booking is confirmed. Please check your booking details carefully before completing a tour.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        When will I get my refund?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Refunds will immediately be submitted to the bank (if applicable). It usually takes up to 10 business days to process the refund payment and transfer the funds into customer account. Some banks can take up to 15-30 days or until the next billing cycle. Refund will be converted to your local currency by your credit card company.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Can I request a refund if I am late to the tour?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Late arrival will be treated as no show resulting in no date change and no refund will be paid. Please arrive early at the assemble point as stated by the tour operator.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h4>Tour Operators</h4>
<ol>
    <li>
        Who can sign up as a tour operator?
        <ul>
            <li>
                Travosaur works with professional tour operators across Australia. We accept private or freelance tour operator provided if you have an ABN number and some great tours to list on Travosaur. We will screen all application and due to the large number of applications, we only respond to applications that have successfully passed our screening process. If you would like to be one, please sign up here.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Is it free to list my tours on Travosaur?
        <ul>
            <li>
                It’s free to list your tours on Travosaur. However, we do charge 2% for each success booking made. No Booking = No Commission. If you would like to be part of us, please sign up here.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        How to list my tours?
        <ul>
            <li>
                You must register with us to list your tours on Travosaur. Our industry leading and user friendly platform is your best place to list and manage your tours online. You will also get the insights and some ideas of what are really matters to your customers.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>